race.comment: MASTRETTA (6) deserved her easy CL2 win here third-up making strong further improvement. She worked over to lead them up and jumps from an inside gate in this. Carries half a kilo less and can go on with the job. RUNAWAY STATEMENT (7) resumes and has switched from the Stokes yard in Adelaide to Brendan McShane. Is right up to this she's presented on song and is proven fresh. The top hoop is booked, suggesting she's pleasing. The betting will be key. RUBBLE 'N' FUDD (1) was heavily bet to win here first-up in stronger and looked a run short. He's won 4/7, including second-up. He should be right in it. ESPRIT DIVA (5) would be a hope on her effort here two back in better grade and maps well.
